.TH hsh 1 "December 2023" "Version 1.0" "hsh Manual"

.SH NAME
hsh \- simple shell for executing commands

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple shell program that reads commands from the user and executes them.

.SH FUNCTIONS
.IP \fBread_command()\fR
Reads a command from the standard input.

.IP \fBparse_arguments(command, args)\fR
Parses the command string into arguments.

.IP \fBexecute_command(command)\fR
Executes the given command string.

.IP \fBprint_environment()\fR
Prints the environment variables.

.IP \fBexecute_from_path(command, args)\fR
Executes the command from the PATH environment variable.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The functions return the exit status of the executed command or -1 if an error occurs.

.SH EXAMPLES
To execute a command, use the hsh program as follows:

.B hsh
command

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Sayyar Heydarov and Hamid Hamidbeyli.


.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR execve (2),
.BR getenv (3).

